00:12:38.930 --> 00:12:44.800 align:middle line:90%


00:12:44.800 --> 00:12:47.570 align:middle line:84%
>> When I heard about these
buses that you could get

00:12:47.570 --> 00:12:54.150 align:middle line:84%
on and go from England to
Nepal, drive through all these

00:12:54.150 --> 00:12:55.790 align:middle line:90%
countries.

00:12:55.790 --> 00:12:59.150 align:middle line:84%
Think about driving through
like Iraq and Iran, Afghanistan,

00:12:59.150 --> 00:12:59.950 align:middle line:90%
Pakistan.

00:12:59.950 --> 00:13:20.679 align:middle line:90%


00:13:20.679 --> 00:13:22.220 align:middle line:84%
>> We didn't think
about the dangers.

00:13:22.220 --> 00:13:23.940 align:middle line:90%
We didn't think about the risks.

00:13:23.940 --> 00:13:25.440 align:middle line:90%
It was what we had to do.

00:13:25.440 --> 00:13:26.410 align:middle line:90%
We had to do.

00:13:26.410 --> 00:13:30.610 align:middle line:90%


00:13:30.610 --> 00:13:34.560 align:middle line:84%
>> I had absolutely no idea
about Hinduism or Buddhism

00:13:34.560 --> 00:13:35.650 align:middle line:90%
or nothing, really.

00:13:35.650 --> 00:13:39.070 align:middle line:84%
And then on the way,
I met one American,

00:13:39.070 --> 00:13:42.570 align:middle line:84%
and he had been already with
the Tibetan Lamas in Nepal.

00:13:42.570 --> 00:13:46.250 align:middle line:84%
And he was talking to me a
lot about Kathmandu and Nepal

00:13:46.250 --> 00:13:48.720 align:middle line:84%
and all the Tibetans, and the
Tibetans, and the Tibetans.

00:13:48.720 --> 00:13:51.800 align:middle line:90%


00:13:51.800 --> 00:13:53.954 align:middle line:90%
>> Eye on the Himalayas.

00:13:53.954 --> 00:13:58.930 align:middle line:84%
Tibet's religious tradition is
personified by the Dalai Lama.

00:13:58.930 --> 00:14:00.860 align:middle line:84%
These are films
of the Dalai Lama,

00:14:00.860 --> 00:14:02.430 align:middle line:90%
taken in less troubled times.

00:14:02.430 --> 00:14:08.040 align:middle line:90%


00:14:08.040 --> 00:14:11.370 align:middle line:84%
News now reaches the
world that 20,000 Tibetans

00:14:11.370 --> 00:14:14.670 align:middle line:84%
have risen with him against
their Chinese Overlords.

00:14:14.670 --> 00:14:17.370 align:middle line:90%


00:14:17.370 --> 00:14:19.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Two days after
the Lhasa uprising,

00:14:19.830 --> 00:14:24.300 align:middle line:84%
the Dalai Lama escaped
from his palace.

00:14:24.300 --> 00:14:27.030 align:middle line:84%
The Dalai Lama's escape
sparked an exodus

00:14:27.030 --> 00:14:29.790 align:middle line:84%
of refugees as tens of
thousands of Tibetans

00:14:29.790 --> 00:14:33.280 align:middle line:90%
followed him into exile.

00:14:33.280 --> 00:14:37.040 align:middle line:10%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:14:37.040 --> 00:14:42.200 align:middle line:10%
>> In 1959, he came from Tibet.

00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:46.070 align:middle line:10%
>> It took almost one
month, all time walking.

00:14:46.070 --> 00:14:47.090 align:middle line:90%
We walk all the way.

00:14:47.090 --> 00:14:51.220 align:middle line:90%


00:14:51.220 --> 00:14:55.250 align:middle line:10%
>> And then sometimes we
came through snow mountain,

00:14:55.250 --> 00:14:57.665 align:middle line:10%
day and night, on horses.

00:14:57.665 --> 00:15:04.020 align:middle line:90%


00:15:04.020 --> 00:15:07.204 align:middle line:10%
Sometimes we were caught
by the Chinese Army

00:15:07.204 --> 00:15:10.462 align:middle line:10%
and they put us for a
short period in prison.

00:15:10.462 --> 00:15:21.154 align:middle line:90%


00:15:21.154 --> 00:15:23.480 align:middle line:10%
>> When the Dalai
Lama left Tibet,

00:15:23.480 --> 00:15:26.170 align:middle line:10%
I was still in high school.

00:15:26.170 --> 00:15:28.630 align:middle line:10%
And somehow I heard
the news on the radio

00:15:28.630 --> 00:15:30.910 align:middle line:10%
that he had left Tibet
and entered India.

00:15:30.910 --> 00:15:33.880 align:middle line:84%
And somehow there was
some sense that this

00:15:33.880 --> 00:15:35.200 align:middle line:90%
was something special.

00:15:35.200 --> 00:15:38.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Thousands crowd the railway
station in New Delhi to welcome

00:15:38.860 --> 00:15:40.240 align:middle line:90%
the Dalai Lama.

00:15:40.240 --> 00:15:43.840 align:middle line:90%
>> [TIBETAN SPEECH]

00:15:43.840 --> 00:15:47.020 align:middle line:84%
>> Speaking in Tibetan,
the Dalai Lama charges that

00:15:47.020 --> 00:15:49.880 align:middle line:84%
the Tibetan people are
being exterminated.

00:15:49.880 --> 00:15:52.600 align:middle line:84%
That their culture and
religion are being stamped out.

00:15:52.600 --> 00:16:10.640 align:middle line:90%


00:16:10.640 --> 00:16:13.680 align:middle line:10%
>> Actually this
cultural revolution,

00:16:13.680 --> 00:16:18.420 align:middle line:10%
destruction of Tibet, actually
proved for us the real value

00:16:18.420 --> 00:16:22.610 align:middle line:10%
of Buddha's teachings.

00:16:22.610 --> 00:16:32.011 align:middle line:90%


00:16:32.011 --> 00:16:34.157 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS] OK.

00:16:34.157 --> 00:16:34.957 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:16:34.957 --> 00:16:44.777 align:middle line:90%


00:16:44.777 --> 00:16:47.060 align:middle line:84%
>> When I first
arrived in Dharamsala,

00:16:47.060 --> 00:16:49.570 align:middle line:84%
I struggled up the
hill with my rucksack.

00:16:49.570 --> 00:16:54.560 align:middle line:84%
I came to a large rock on
which were written the letters,

00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:57.110 align:middle line:84%
[NON-ENGLISH],, but I
didn't know what they were.

00:16:57.110 --> 00:17:00.950 align:middle line:90%


00:17:00.950 --> 00:17:02.470 align:middle line:90%
If we go down to this--

00:17:02.470 --> 00:17:03.936 align:middle line:90%
through here.

00:17:03.936 --> 00:17:05.589 align:middle line:90%
>> But this is to the--

00:17:05.589 --> 00:17:07.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, look at that.

00:17:07.500 --> 00:17:09.869 align:middle line:90%
I lived in there, on my--

00:17:09.869 --> 00:17:13.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Dharamsala in those days was
really just flattened tin cans

00:17:13.280 --> 00:17:15.530 align:middle line:90%
and little shops.

00:17:15.530 --> 00:17:20.400 align:middle line:10%
People selling their
old clothes and stuff.

00:17:20.400 --> 00:17:22.069 align:middle line:90%
>> It was a one-horse town.

00:17:22.069 --> 00:17:25.230 align:middle line:84%
There were no Jeeps,
there were no cars.

00:17:25.230 --> 00:17:29.310 align:middle line:84%
>> This is this Tibetan
amalah who I loved.

00:17:29.310 --> 00:17:30.120 align:middle line:90%
That's me.

00:17:30.120 --> 00:17:33.240 align:middle line:84%
It was really the
Tibetans that got me--

00:17:33.240 --> 00:17:36.210 align:middle line:84%
the main thing was just
the warmth of the people.

00:17:36.210 --> 00:17:38.760 align:middle line:90%
That feeling of joy.

00:17:38.760 --> 00:17:41.760 align:middle line:84%
And I could not figure it
out because most of them

00:17:41.760 --> 00:17:44.170 align:middle line:90%
had lost everything.

00:17:44.170 --> 00:17:46.590 align:middle line:84%
Some of them had seen
their own families

00:17:46.590 --> 00:17:50.320 align:middle line:90%
killed in front of them.

00:17:50.320 --> 00:17:52.030 align:middle line:90%
>> They were working on roads.

00:17:52.030 --> 00:17:55.750 align:middle line:84%
That was what I found amazing
about Tibetans is this ability

00:17:55.750 --> 00:18:04.140 align:middle line:84%
to adjust from being a prince
or a nobleman to having nothing.

00:18:04.140 --> 00:18:10.230 align:middle line:90%


00:18:10.230 --> 00:18:13.350 align:middle line:10%
We found that all of our
preconceptions, the things we

00:18:13.350 --> 00:18:16.920 align:middle line:10%
had been trained
as, as children, as

00:18:16.920 --> 00:18:22.450 align:middle line:10%
to what was proper, what was
desirable, were not desirable.

00:18:22.450 --> 00:18:26.500 align:middle line:90%


00:18:26.500 --> 00:18:29.340 align:middle line:10%
>> I became close and attached
to Dilgo Khyentse Rinpoche

00:18:29.340 --> 00:18:33.570 align:middle line:10%
and spent, I don't know, 13
years now, non-stop with him.

00:18:33.570 --> 00:18:36.920 align:middle line:10%
>> There's a Tibetan expression
that you cannot stand parting

00:18:36.920 --> 00:18:39.320 align:middle line:10%
away from someone like
Dilgo Khyentse Rinpoche.

00:18:39.320 --> 00:18:42.070 align:middle line:84%
Even like in the
day, just to go away,

00:18:42.070 --> 00:18:45.700 align:middle line:84%
you feel you are missing
something very precious.

00:18:45.700 --> 00:18:47.680 align:middle line:84%
And that's not very
common in life.

00:18:47.680 --> 00:18:53.910 align:middle line:90%


00:18:53.910 --> 00:18:57.760 align:middle line:84%
>> When I got to Kathmandu, I
heard that there was this Lama

00:18:57.760 --> 00:19:00.210 align:middle line:90%
there named Karmapa.

00:19:00.210 --> 00:19:05.380 align:middle line:84%
I was really fascinated by him
and started going to see him.

00:19:05.380 --> 00:19:08.820 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought well, he's a
monk, I should become a nun.

00:19:08.820 --> 00:19:11.330 align:middle line:84%
That would be
following his example.

00:19:11.330 --> 00:19:13.020 align:middle line:84%
That was really
why I became a nun.

00:19:13.020 --> 00:19:19.430 align:middle line:90%


00:19:19.430 --> 00:19:23.580 align:middle line:10%
>> When I went first time to
Nepal and the first time I met

00:19:23.580 --> 00:19:25.750 align:middle line:10%
the Dharma that
was in Kopan Hill.

00:19:25.750 --> 00:19:28.540 align:middle line:10%


00:19:28.540 --> 00:19:31.850 align:middle line:10%
There was a Lama teaching,
and this was Lama Lama Thubten

00:19:31.850 --> 00:19:32.650 align:middle line:10%
Yeshe.

00:19:32.650 --> 00:19:36.220 align:middle line:10%
And he would teach in English.

00:19:36.220 --> 00:19:40.210 align:middle line:10%
>> You cannot jump into such
inner freedom, sort of like,

00:19:40.210 --> 00:19:42.160 align:middle line:10%
cannot jump.

00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:44.517 align:middle line:10%
>> He had this kind
of odd English.

00:19:44.517 --> 00:19:46.100 align:middle line:10%
>> You cannot jump
such inner freedom.

00:19:46.100 --> 00:19:47.516 align:middle line:84%
>> That he'd learned
from hippies.

00:19:47.516 --> 00:19:50.000 align:middle line:90%


00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:53.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Lama Yeshe and Lama Zopa
first taught Westerners in '71.

00:19:53.560 --> 00:19:56.890 align:middle line:90%


00:19:56.890 --> 00:19:59.170 align:middle line:10%
And it just started to blossom.

00:19:59.170 --> 00:20:02.250 align:middle line:10%
These Westerners climbing
up the hill over rice

00:20:02.250 --> 00:20:03.660 align:middle line:10%
paddies to get up there.

00:20:03.660 --> 00:20:11.500 align:middle line:90%


00:20:11.500 --> 00:20:13.360 align:middle line:84%
We had a month of
teachings and then

00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:16.164 align:middle line:84%
contemplating on
these teachings.

00:20:16.164 --> 00:20:22.790 align:middle line:10%
>> Although, since you were
born, up until now, you said,

00:20:22.790 --> 00:20:24.060 align:middle line:10%
my mind is that.

00:20:24.060 --> 00:20:25.430 align:middle line:10%
My mind is that.

00:20:25.430 --> 00:20:28.560 align:middle line:10%
You have no idea
what is your mind.

00:20:28.560 --> 00:20:30.986 align:middle line:10%
Isn't that silly?

00:20:30.986 --> 00:20:34.370 align:middle line:10%
Every day, using "my mind is
that, that, blah, blah, blah."

00:20:34.370 --> 00:20:38.730 align:middle line:10%
But you don't know what is
it, your nature of your mind.

00:20:38.730 --> 00:20:42.710 align:middle line:84%
>> And that was a shock for
me, because I had never thought

00:20:42.710 --> 00:20:47.950 align:middle line:84%
that you could have
wisdom without thinking.

00:20:47.950 --> 00:20:49.250 align:middle line:90%
And I was sick of thinking.

00:20:49.250 --> 00:20:52.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I was completely
sick of my thoughts

00:20:52.020 --> 00:20:59.570 align:middle line:84%
and my mental state, and I was
looking for some breakthrough.

00:20:59.570 --> 00:21:00.880 align:middle line:90%
>> So that really had--

00:21:00.880 --> 00:21:03.410 align:middle line:84%
it really gave you
the opportunity

00:21:03.410 --> 00:21:07.380 align:middle line:84%
to work with the
nitty-gritty of the mind.

00:21:07.380 --> 00:21:10.070 align:middle line:84%
And I think that one of
the big realizations for me

00:21:10.070 --> 00:21:12.219 align:middle line:84%
during that month was
yes, the mind does

00:21:12.219 --> 00:21:13.385 align:middle line:90%
have the capacity to change.

00:21:13.385 --> 00:21:16.135 align:middle line:90%


00:21:16.135 --> 00:21:17.614 align:middle line:90%
[SIGHS]

00:21:17.614 --> 00:21:30.432 align:middle line:90%


00:21:30.432 --> 00:21:33.883 align:middle line:10%
[BELL RINGING]

00:21:33.883 --> 00:21:36.841 align:middle line:90%


00:21:36.841 --> 00:21:40.830 align:middle line:84%
>> I've read quite a
few books about Tibet.

00:21:40.830 --> 00:21:44.240 align:middle line:10%
Tibet was somewhere in
space, kind of remote.

00:21:44.240 --> 00:21:46.670 align:middle line:10%
But then news got
around amongst people

00:21:46.670 --> 00:21:48.420 align:middle line:10%
that there was going
to be a Lama that was

00:21:48.420 --> 00:21:51.450 align:middle line:10%
going to turn up in Kensington.

00:21:51.450 --> 00:21:54.730 align:middle line:84%
To have a Lama turn up
was quite extraordinary

00:21:54.730 --> 00:21:56.620 align:middle line:84%
because we never imagined
that would happen.

00:21:56.620 --> 00:22:02.680 align:middle line:90%


00:22:02.680 --> 00:22:05.550 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I was in the
market for a teacher.

00:22:05.550 --> 00:22:08.250 align:middle line:10%
And an old friend
wrote to me and said,

00:22:08.250 --> 00:22:11.070 align:middle line:10%
I'm coming to Los Angeles
with this great teacher,

00:22:11.070 --> 00:22:14.580 align:middle line:10%
and you must,
absolutely must see him.

00:22:14.580 --> 00:22:18.420 align:middle line:10%
He spoke in a downtown, really
shabby, old, Embassy Theater,

00:22:18.420 --> 00:22:20.310 align:middle line:10%
I think it was called.

00:22:20.310 --> 00:22:24.420 align:middle line:10%
And he walked on the stage,
and I was electrified.

00:22:24.420 --> 00:22:27.970 align:middle line:10%
>> Sit on the cushion.

00:22:27.970 --> 00:22:30.630 align:middle line:84%
But don't make a
big deal about that,

00:22:30.630 --> 00:22:33.810 align:middle line:90%
now you are going to meditate.

00:22:33.810 --> 00:22:39.060 align:middle line:90%
Just sit down and relax.

00:22:39.060 --> 00:22:43.130 align:middle line:84%
>> When I met Trungpa Rinpoche,
I probably cried for two hours.

00:22:43.130 --> 00:22:46.350 align:middle line:84%
You know, a sense of
having met something

00:22:46.350 --> 00:22:50.460 align:middle line:84%
that was so deeply precious to
me and not having any idea why.

00:22:50.460 --> 00:23:01.010 align:middle line:90%


00:23:01.010 --> 00:23:05.065 align:middle line:84%
>> Trungpa swept through
America just like a rocket.

00:23:05.065 --> 00:23:07.860 align:middle line:90%


00:23:07.860 --> 00:23:09.800 align:middle line:84%
He starts traveling
all over the country.

00:23:09.800 --> 00:23:12.650 align:middle line:90%


00:23:12.650 --> 00:23:14.890 align:middle line:84%
He teaches right
away, all the time.

00:23:14.890 --> 00:23:18.830 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:18.830 --> 00:23:22.550 align:middle line:84%
He knew when the Chinese
invaded Tibet it wasn't just

00:23:22.550 --> 00:23:26.390 align:middle line:84%
a question of taking the
teachings out and putting them

00:23:26.390 --> 00:23:29.540 align:middle line:84%
under your robe and getting
the hell out of the country.

00:23:29.540 --> 00:23:35.390 align:middle line:84%
It was a question of bringing
that living wisdom to a brand

00:23:35.390 --> 00:23:38.660 align:middle line:84%
new culture, thousands
of miles and a completely

00:23:38.660 --> 00:23:40.190 align:middle line:90%
different language away.

00:23:40.190 --> 00:23:43.730 align:middle line:84%
>> And giving up, opening,
surrendering from that point

00:23:43.730 --> 00:23:47.120 align:middle line:84%
of view actually pays
a very important part.

00:23:47.120 --> 00:23:50.780 align:middle line:84%
Because finally, you
begin to actually let

00:23:50.780 --> 00:23:53.630 align:middle line:90%
go of your aggression.

00:23:53.630 --> 00:23:56.750 align:middle line:84%
And you begin to
hear much better

00:23:56.750 --> 00:23:59.540 align:middle line:84%
and see much better
when you give

00:23:59.540 --> 00:24:02.780 align:middle line:84%
more and more of this
uptightness or holding back--

00:24:02.780 --> 00:24:06.410 align:middle line:84%
>> A Dharma that was not
some kind of specialized,

00:24:06.410 --> 00:24:11.060 align:middle line:84%
cloistered, monastic Dharma,
but a Dharma that was fully

00:24:11.060 --> 00:24:13.140 align:middle line:84%
integrated with
society and with life.

00:24:13.140 --> 00:24:16.530 align:middle line:90%


00:24:16.530 --> 00:24:18.660 align:middle line:90%
>> He dove into Western life.

00:24:18.660 --> 00:24:20.850 align:middle line:84%
He drank, he smoked,
he broke all the rules.

00:24:20.850 --> 00:24:23.810 align:middle line:90%


00:24:23.810 --> 00:24:28.530 align:middle line:84%
>> People were always
so outraged by him.

00:24:28.530 --> 00:24:29.870 align:middle line:10%
>> He was a fantastic artist.

00:24:29.870 --> 00:24:32.900 align:middle line:10%
As a calligrapher, as a flower
arranger, as a photographer,

00:24:32.900 --> 00:24:35.470 align:middle line:10%
as a writer, as a poet.

00:24:35.470 --> 00:24:38.150 align:middle line:84%
And that was one of the things
that was enormously attractive

00:24:38.150 --> 00:24:38.954 align:middle line:90%
about him.

00:24:38.954 --> 00:24:48.840 align:middle line:90%


00:24:48.840 --> 00:24:53.175 align:middle line:84%
>> An interesting part of it is
this is in Tibetan tradition,

00:24:53.175 --> 00:24:56.170 align:middle line:90%
there's no word for artist.

00:24:56.170 --> 00:24:58.750 align:middle line:84%
>> And so he was immediately
working with a new energy.

00:24:58.750 --> 00:25:02.890 align:middle line:84%
The energy that said,
OK, tell it to us.

00:25:02.890 --> 00:25:03.740 align:middle line:90%
Give it to us.

00:25:03.740 --> 00:25:04.390 align:middle line:90%
Tell us what to do.

00:25:04.390 --> 00:25:05.265 align:middle line:90%
We'll make it happen.

00:25:05.265 --> 00:25:12.870 align:middle line:90%


00:25:12.870 --> 00:25:16.320 align:middle line:84%
And he had every confidence
that we would get it.

00:25:16.320 --> 00:25:26.820 align:middle line:90%


00:25:26.820 --> 00:25:30.500 align:middle line:84%
>> I spent a lot of time in
some kind of retreat context

00:25:30.500 --> 00:25:34.220 align:middle line:90%
and also traveling with him.

00:25:34.220 --> 00:25:37.520 align:middle line:84%
And then I'd go off and be a
crazy person, smuggling cocaine

00:25:37.520 --> 00:25:38.960 align:middle line:90%
in South America.

00:25:38.960 --> 00:25:42.260 align:middle line:84%
It was actually coming back from
Japan with Trungpa Rinpoche,

00:25:42.260 --> 00:25:45.140 align:middle line:90%
that I got pulled aside.

00:25:45.140 --> 00:25:48.290 align:middle line:84%
I knew I was either
going to go on the run,

00:25:48.290 --> 00:25:50.750 align:middle line:84%
or I was going to prison for
a long time at that point.

00:25:50.750 --> 00:25:53.270 align:middle line:84%
And he told me I should
stay and face it.

00:25:53.270 --> 00:25:55.700 align:middle line:84%
And he said that even if I
was in prison for a long time,

00:25:55.700 --> 00:25:57.408 align:middle line:84%
I could still practice,
and I could still

00:25:57.408 --> 00:25:58.850 align:middle line:90%
work with him as my teacher.

