00:50:11.130 --> 00:50:14.130 align:middle line:10%
that it's not very good
for Western students

00:50:14.130 --> 00:50:18.390 align:middle line:10%
to try to encourage them through
a path that has so much form.

00:50:18.390 --> 00:50:20.340 align:middle line:84%
And the reason is that
their lives are already

00:50:20.340 --> 00:50:22.624 align:middle line:90%
so packed with form.

00:50:22.624 --> 00:50:23.790 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't that way in Tibet.

00:50:23.790 --> 00:50:26.010 align:middle line:84%
In Tibet, there's a lot
more space as a culture.

00:50:26.010 --> 00:50:27.150 align:middle line:90%
But in the West, it is.

00:50:27.150 --> 00:50:28.680 align:middle line:84%
Every minute is
filled with form.

00:50:28.680 --> 00:50:32.070 align:middle line:84%
So give them more form doesn't
really seem to work that well.

00:50:32.070 --> 00:50:36.010 align:middle line:90%


00:50:36.010 --> 00:50:39.000 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to
do a practice now

00:50:39.000 --> 00:50:42.672 align:middle line:84%
that involves breathing
into the lower belly.

00:50:42.672 --> 00:50:43.630 align:middle line:90%
Feel the space opening.

00:50:43.630 --> 00:50:47.420 align:middle line:90%


00:50:47.420 --> 00:50:48.220 align:middle line:90%
In breath.

00:50:48.220 --> 00:50:50.760 align:middle line:90%


00:50:50.760 --> 00:50:52.400 align:middle line:90%
Filling the lower belly.

00:50:52.400 --> 00:50:55.430 align:middle line:90%
Medium to full breath.

00:50:55.430 --> 00:50:57.800 align:middle line:84%
Through the body
work, what we find is

00:50:57.800 --> 00:50:59.610 align:middle line:84%
it gets Western people
out of their heads.

00:50:59.610 --> 00:51:01.940 align:middle line:90%
--notice the sense of emptiness.

00:51:01.940 --> 00:51:03.920 align:middle line:84%
And when you live in
your body in that way,

00:51:03.920 --> 00:51:07.760 align:middle line:84%
it's so much more compelling
and liberating than thinking.

00:51:07.760 --> 00:51:15.400 align:middle line:90%


00:51:15.400 --> 00:51:18.240 align:middle line:84%
>> I knew I really wanted
to do this retreat center.

00:51:18.240 --> 00:51:24.580 align:middle line:90%


00:51:24.580 --> 00:51:28.870 align:middle line:84%
From the age of 19, I'd
always been asking permission

00:51:28.870 --> 00:51:30.430 align:middle line:90%
to my teachers.

00:51:30.430 --> 00:51:32.770 align:middle line:10%
But I felt that I had
a different experience

00:51:32.770 --> 00:51:39.290 align:middle line:10%
as a Western woman, and
that I needed to honor that.

00:51:39.290 --> 00:51:43.090 align:middle line:84%
I had to make my own
decisions and my own mistakes

00:51:43.090 --> 00:51:46.510 align:middle line:84%
and see what happened, at
least here at Tara Mandala.

00:51:46.510 --> 00:51:52.850 align:middle line:90%


00:51:52.850 --> 00:51:56.870 align:middle line:10%
There's a sort of neo-generation
of people that really realize

00:51:56.870 --> 00:51:59.570 align:middle line:10%
they don't want to go
into the corporate world,

00:51:59.570 --> 00:52:03.090 align:middle line:10%
and that they want something
substantial and inner.

00:52:03.090 --> 00:52:03.890 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:52:03.890 --> 00:52:06.306 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's like, I get there,
but then it's like my heart

00:52:06.306 --> 00:52:07.130 align:middle line:90%
stops again.

00:52:07.130 --> 00:52:08.540 align:middle line:90%
And I can't do anything--

00:52:08.540 --> 00:52:10.910 align:middle line:84%
>> And those people
are attracted here,

00:52:10.910 --> 00:52:15.022 align:middle line:84%
and then they become
practitioners.

00:52:15.022 --> 00:52:17.974 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:52:17.974 --> 00:52:27.840 align:middle line:90%


00:52:27.840 --> 00:52:29.570 align:middle line:84%
I'm kind of a funny
combination of being

00:52:29.570 --> 00:52:35.430 align:middle line:84%
very traditional and at the
same time, very experimental.

00:52:35.430 --> 00:52:39.570 align:middle line:90%


00:52:39.570 --> 00:52:45.100 align:middle line:10%
>> You get angry, sad, fierce.

00:52:45.100 --> 00:52:49.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Angry and sad and fierce.

00:52:49.790 --> 00:52:53.180 align:middle line:84%
It can't be Tibetan
Buddhism forever.

00:52:53.180 --> 00:52:55.490 align:middle line:84%
You know, it has to become
the Vagrayana tradition

00:52:55.490 --> 00:52:57.275 align:middle line:90%
as it's expressed in the West.

00:52:57.275 --> 00:53:02.150 align:middle line:90%


00:53:02.150 --> 00:53:04.320 align:middle line:84%
But I always struggle
with these questions

00:53:04.320 --> 00:53:06.510 align:middle line:84%
because I have such a
respect for the tradition.

00:53:06.510 --> 00:53:09.420 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:53:09.420 --> 00:53:14.170 align:middle line:84%
I don't want it to be
harmed or diminished.

00:53:14.170 --> 00:53:16.956 align:middle line:84%
And I want to make sure
the depth is happening.

00:53:16.956 --> 00:53:20.610 align:middle line:90%


00:53:20.610 --> 00:53:23.918 align:middle line:84%
Tara Mandala, that's my
primary goal is depth practice.

00:53:23.918 --> 00:53:28.760 align:middle line:90%


00:53:28.760 --> 00:53:32.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Since Sangha is like family.

00:53:32.420 --> 00:53:37.730 align:middle line:10%
Every Sangha, every community,
have their own personalities.

00:53:37.730 --> 00:53:41.480 align:middle line:90%


00:53:41.480 --> 00:53:44.095 align:middle line:84%
Basically, there's
something for everybody.

00:53:44.095 --> 00:53:48.550 align:middle line:90%


00:53:48.550 --> 00:53:51.900 align:middle line:10%
My love of Buddhism was one
of first memories that I have.

00:53:51.900 --> 00:53:55.507 align:middle line:90%


00:53:55.507 --> 00:53:59.220 align:middle line:10%
I believed for a
long time, to be

00:53:59.220 --> 00:54:03.520 align:middle line:10%
spiritual was to be very
serious and to not enjoy life.

00:54:03.520 --> 00:54:08.560 align:middle line:84%
So I had lots of those concepts
and ideas that I had to drop.

00:54:08.560 --> 00:54:11.740 align:middle line:90%


00:54:11.740 --> 00:54:15.580 align:middle line:84%
And then the way
I'm teaching, I let

00:54:15.580 --> 00:54:19.190 align:middle line:90%
go of a lot of beautiful forms.

00:54:19.190 --> 00:54:24.350 align:middle line:84%
It requires tremendous sense
of if our activities to have

00:54:24.350 --> 00:54:27.900 align:middle line:90%
lots of images, big ultra.

00:54:27.900 --> 00:54:36.040 align:middle line:84%
So I'm quite lazy, and also,
in some sense, a minimalist.

00:54:36.040 --> 00:54:39.320 align:middle line:84%
It's not me delivering
another lecture.

00:54:39.320 --> 00:54:43.940 align:middle line:90%
This is about going inside.

00:54:43.940 --> 00:54:49.100 align:middle line:84%
Open our heart and be
honest to ourselves.

00:54:49.100 --> 00:54:51.650 align:middle line:84%
One of the questions
that we might like to ask

00:54:51.650 --> 00:54:54.620 align:middle line:90%
is why am I not free right now?

00:54:54.620 --> 00:55:00.300 align:middle line:90%


00:55:00.300 --> 00:55:05.450 align:middle line:84%
So I let go of lots of forms
and focusing more the heart

00:55:05.450 --> 00:55:08.930 align:middle line:84%
of Buddhist teachings,
which is very profound,

00:55:08.930 --> 00:55:09.950 align:middle line:90%
yet it is simple.

00:55:09.950 --> 00:55:26.710 align:middle line:90%


00:55:26.710 --> 00:55:29.440 align:middle line:10%
>> You know, the foundations,
the Four Noble Truths,

00:55:29.440 --> 00:55:34.330 align:middle line:10%
there is absolutely no way
you can get any understanding

00:55:34.330 --> 00:55:39.040 align:middle line:10%
of the Dharma without it really
being sort of squeezed from

00:55:39.040 --> 00:55:42.300 align:middle line:10%
the essence of a thorough
understanding of the Four Noble

00:55:42.300 --> 00:55:44.460 align:middle line:10%
Truths.

00:55:44.460 --> 00:55:46.850 align:middle line:84%
>> What are the
Four Noble Truths?

00:55:46.850 --> 00:55:48.735 align:middle line:84%
In four words,
they're suffering,

00:55:48.735 --> 00:55:50.860 align:middle line:84%
the cause of suffering,
the cessation of suffering,

00:55:50.860 --> 00:55:51.858 align:middle line:90%
and the path.

00:55:51.858 --> 00:55:55.351 align:middle line:90%
[SIRENS]

00:55:55.351 --> 00:55:58.345 align:middle line:90%


00:55:58.345 --> 00:56:01.339 align:middle line:90%
[BABY CRYING]

00:56:01.339 --> 00:56:04.333 align:middle line:90%


00:56:04.333 --> 00:56:07.327 align:middle line:90%
[TRAFFIC NOISES]

00:56:07.327 --> 00:56:18.185 align:middle line:90%


00:56:18.185 --> 00:56:19.560 align:middle line:10%
>> From the Buddhist
perspective,

00:56:19.560 --> 00:56:23.360 align:middle line:10%
we're all trapped in this sort
of wheel of existence called

00:56:23.360 --> 00:56:24.160 align:middle line:10%
Samsara.

00:56:24.160 --> 00:56:30.290 align:middle line:90%


00:56:30.290 --> 00:56:33.550 align:middle line:84%
The idea is this is sort
of the First Noble Truth,

00:56:33.550 --> 00:56:35.430 align:middle line:90%
that life is suffering.

00:56:35.430 --> 00:56:36.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Going about
things in the old,

00:56:36.940 --> 00:56:39.695 align:middle line:84%
ordinary way will lead
to suffering, period.

00:56:39.695 --> 00:56:44.240 align:middle line:90%


00:56:44.240 --> 00:56:48.090 align:middle line:90%
Brookeye Productions.

00:56:48.090 --> 00:56:53.010 align:middle line:84%
I feel like people spend
so much time focusing

00:56:53.010 --> 00:56:57.020 align:middle line:84%
on their career or their bodies
or what they look like, I mean,

00:56:57.020 --> 00:56:59.370 align:middle line:90%
hello.

00:56:59.370 --> 00:57:02.055 align:middle line:84%
People, we spend such little
time focused on our minds.

00:57:02.055 --> 00:57:04.600 align:middle line:90%


00:57:04.600 --> 00:57:07.030 align:middle line:90%
Today's my last day of work.

00:57:07.030 --> 00:57:09.180 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to meet my other
friends for going away

00:57:09.180 --> 00:57:14.550 align:middle line:84%
drinks and dinner, and it's
going to be really fun.

00:57:14.550 --> 00:57:16.590 align:middle line:84%
And I just can't believe
that I'm actually done,

00:57:16.590 --> 00:57:20.530 align:middle line:84%
and that it's
actually happening.

00:57:20.530 --> 00:57:23.200 align:middle line:84%
Because then I hope I don't
screw up and miss my flight

00:57:23.200 --> 00:57:24.000 align:middle line:90%
or anything.

00:57:24.000 --> 00:57:25.625 align:middle line:84%
I need to cancel my
Equinox membership.

00:57:25.625 --> 00:57:26.920 align:middle line:90%
I need to--

00:57:26.920 --> 00:57:30.280 align:middle line:84%
>> The First Noble Truth
is a quality of pervasive

00:57:30.280 --> 00:57:33.000 align:middle line:90%
dissatisfaction, let's say.

00:57:33.000 --> 00:57:37.520 align:middle line:84%
That agitation and
discomfort are inevitable.

00:57:37.520 --> 00:57:39.370 align:middle line:10%
Suffering is inevitable.

00:57:39.370 --> 00:57:41.930 align:middle line:10%
We're all going to die.

00:57:41.930 --> 00:57:43.120 align:middle line:90%
We know it intellectually.

00:57:43.120 --> 00:57:43.920 align:middle line:90%
Yes, sure.

00:57:43.920 --> 00:57:45.600 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to die.

00:57:45.600 --> 00:57:49.714 align:middle line:90%
But tonight?

00:57:49.714 --> 00:57:51.706 align:middle line:90%
[DOOR OPENING]

00:57:51.706 --> 00:57:52.898 align:middle line:90%


00:57:52.898 --> 00:57:53.698 align:middle line:90%
>> Merci.

00:57:53.698 --> 00:57:54.196 align:middle line:90%
Merci.

00:57:54.196 --> 00:57:55.192 align:middle line:90%
>> Merci.

00:57:55.192 --> 00:57:58.180 align:middle line:84%
>> How do you feel about
me going on a retreat?

00:57:58.180 --> 00:58:02.164 align:middle line:84%
>> I think you're going to
turn into the Unibomber.

00:58:02.164 --> 00:58:04.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Can I have a drink on my tab?

00:58:04.160 --> 00:58:06.710 align:middle line:84%
>> My teacher used
to always say,

00:58:06.710 --> 00:58:11.450 align:middle line:84%
listen to the sound of sadness
and the heightened resonance

00:58:11.450 --> 00:58:12.515 align:middle line:90%
of laughter.

00:58:12.515 --> 00:58:14.000 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:58:14.000 --> 00:58:15.980 align:middle line:90%


00:58:15.980 --> 00:58:18.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Suffering is like that.

00:58:18.140 --> 00:58:24.860 align:middle line:10%
>> I would define suffering as
a condition of the mind that

00:58:24.860 --> 00:58:30.380 align:middle line:10%
involves an inaccurate
perception of reality which

00:58:30.380 --> 00:58:34.200 align:middle line:10%
leads to disturbance that is
in the mind, in the brain,

00:58:34.200 --> 00:58:35.000 align:middle line:10%
and in the body.

00:58:35.000 --> 00:58:38.490 align:middle line:90%


00:58:38.490 --> 00:58:40.640 align:middle line:10%
>> At times, it
seemed like it was--

00:58:40.640 --> 00:58:43.780 align:middle line:10%
I was having a great time.

00:58:43.780 --> 00:58:46.180 align:middle line:84%
But I was really
depressed, really,

00:58:46.180 --> 00:58:49.950 align:middle line:84%
in the back of my
mind, all the time.

00:58:49.950 --> 00:58:56.760 align:middle line:84%
>> What I call the new epidemic
is alienation, loneliness,

00:58:56.760 --> 00:58:58.650 align:middle line:90%
and depression.

00:58:58.650 --> 00:59:01.780 align:middle line:90%
Disconnected feelings.

00:59:01.780 --> 00:59:04.680 align:middle line:90%
Even if everything is--

00:59:04.680 --> 00:59:07.620 align:middle line:84%
in a kind of
pragmatic world, it's

00:59:07.620 --> 00:59:11.603 align:middle line:84%
all taken care of, in one's
mind, lots of suffering.

00:59:11.603 --> 00:59:15.470 align:middle line:90%


00:59:15.470 --> 00:59:20.660 align:middle line:84%
>> The inner experience of my
inner engine racing through

00:59:20.660 --> 00:59:25.262 align:middle line:84%
my day, at its worst, can
be incredibly painful.

00:59:25.262 --> 00:59:27.470 align:middle line:10%
I can move into a mode where
I feel like I'm actually

00:59:27.470 --> 00:59:30.180 align:middle line:10%
perpetuating the problem.

00:59:30.180 --> 00:59:31.590 align:middle line:10%
Like I'm really making it worse.

00:59:31.590 --> 00:59:33.950 align:middle line:84%
And so I go, and I feel
like I'm feeling bad.

00:59:33.950 --> 00:59:34.850 align:middle line:84%
And then I don't
want to feel bad,

00:59:34.850 --> 00:59:36.200 align:middle line:84%
so I kind of reject
the fact that I'm

00:59:36.200 --> 00:59:37.760 align:middle line:84%
feeling bad, which
means I'm not really

00:59:37.760 --> 00:59:39.551 align:middle line:84%
being present with what
I'm really feeling,

00:59:39.551 --> 00:59:40.580 align:middle line:90%
which is feeling bad.

00:59:40.580 --> 00:59:42.538 align:middle line:84%
And then in the meanwhile,
I don't want anybody

00:59:42.538 --> 00:59:44.730 align:middle line:84%
on the outside to know
that I'm suffering.

00:59:44.730 --> 00:59:46.690 align:middle line:84%
So I try to keep a
really cool look.

00:59:46.690 --> 00:59:47.940 align:middle line:90%
Like, hey, everything's fine.

00:59:47.940 --> 00:59:48.740 align:middle line:90%
There's no problem.

00:59:48.740 --> 00:59:52.070 align:middle line:90%


00:59:52.070 --> 00:59:55.700 align:middle line:84%
So I've got my children and
my wife and my colleagues

00:59:55.700 --> 00:59:57.980 align:middle line:84%
that I work with, and
not to mention people

00:59:57.980 --> 00:59:59.480 align:middle line:84%
that are sharing
the road with me,

00:59:59.480 --> 01:00:01.799 align:middle line:84%
as I race down the street
in my car, feeling this way.

01:00:01.799 --> 01:00:03.590 align:middle line:84%
There are like two
screenings on one night.

01:00:03.590 --> 01:00:08.600 align:middle line:90%


01:00:08.600 --> 01:00:12.590 align:middle line:84%
>> About six months ago, I was
applying to business school.

01:00:12.590 --> 01:00:14.430 align:middle line:84%
And I just really
couldn't do it.

01:00:14.430 --> 01:00:17.360 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that
I really wanted

01:00:17.360 --> 01:00:19.280 align:middle line:84%
to do something
else with my life.

01:00:19.280 --> 01:00:22.542 align:middle line:90%


01:00:22.542 --> 01:00:24.740 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to be
gone for five months.

01:00:24.740 --> 01:00:26.390 align:middle line:90%
Long, black sweater-thing.

01:00:26.390 --> 01:00:27.883 align:middle line:90%
Body sweater.

01:00:27.883 --> 01:00:28.683 align:middle line:90%
Body sweater.

01:00:28.683 --> 01:00:29.483 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:00:29.483 --> 01:00:32.330 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to be doing
a retreat by myself,

01:00:32.330 --> 01:00:35.240 align:middle line:90%
basically in the mountains.

01:00:35.240 --> 01:00:37.040 align:middle line:10%
I'm going to go
before I have kids

01:00:37.040 --> 01:00:39.650 align:middle line:10%
and a house and a mortgage.

01:00:39.650 --> 01:00:43.010 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go and
really focus on myself

01:00:43.010 --> 01:00:44.320 align:middle line:90%
before it gets too crazy.

01:00:44.320 --> 01:00:47.320 align:middle line:84%
>> For human beings, it's
very good to understand subtle

01:00:47.320 --> 01:00:51.640 align:middle line:90%
discontentment in every moment.

01:00:51.640 --> 01:00:54.700 align:middle line:84%
And that's the core quality
of suffering that we all have.

01:00:54.700 --> 01:00:58.540 align:middle line:90%


01:00:58.540 --> 01:01:02.160 align:middle line:84%
And so when Dharma says
everything is suffering,

01:01:02.160 --> 01:01:05.995 align:middle line:84%
it's that that you
are looking at.

01:01:05.995 --> 01:01:07.940 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:01:07.940 --> 01:01:09.594 align:middle line:90%
>> (SINGING) Baby, baby--

01:01:09.594 --> 01:01:11.510 align:middle line:84%
no, I want to sing a
song I know the words to.

01:01:11.510 --> 01:01:12.333 align:middle line:90%
>> Put your seat belt on.

01:01:12.333 --> 01:01:14.124 align:middle line:10%
>> I want another song
I know the words to.

01:01:14.124 --> 01:01:15.720 align:middle line:10%
>> I hate this song.

01:01:15.720 --> 01:01:19.620 align:middle line:10%
>> The combination of speed,
of instant gratification,

01:01:19.620 --> 01:01:21.450 align:middle line:10%
it's very painful.

01:01:21.450 --> 01:01:28.200 align:middle line:84%
And all my struggles up to
that point and even today

01:01:28.200 --> 01:01:30.200 align:middle line:84%
deal with the fact
that I want things

01:01:30.200 --> 01:01:32.720 align:middle line:90%
to be fixed in a certain way.

01:01:32.720 --> 01:01:34.790 align:middle line:10%
>> You're entitled to
be happy all the time.

01:01:34.790 --> 01:01:37.910 align:middle line:10%
I mean, that's the fundamental
message of America, I think,

01:01:37.910 --> 01:01:40.040 align:middle line:10%
the American dream.

01:01:40.040 --> 01:01:42.470 align:middle line:84%
If you get more,
you'll be happier.

01:01:42.470 --> 01:01:44.670 align:middle line:84%
If you get different,
you'll be happier.

01:01:44.670 --> 01:01:47.450 align:middle line:84%
And that if you're not
happy, something's wrong,

01:01:47.450 --> 01:01:49.070 align:middle line:90%
and we can fix it.

01:01:49.070 --> 01:01:52.130 align:middle line:84%
We'll fix it with a product,
we'll fix it with medication,

01:01:52.130 --> 01:01:55.730 align:middle line:90%
we'll fix it with entertainment.

01:01:55.730 --> 01:01:58.170 align:middle line:84%
>> The expectation that
if we just try harder,

01:01:58.170 --> 01:02:01.570 align:middle line:84%
we can hit the pleasure
button, and we'll get the M&M

01:02:01.570 --> 01:02:03.530 align:middle line:84%
that's going to
fall down the chute,

01:02:03.530 --> 01:02:07.190 align:middle line:84%
it really is a very compelling
way to spend one's day,

01:02:07.190 --> 01:02:08.740 align:middle line:90%
from one thing to the next.

